You are working on a minimal but serious MLOps project for football World Cup prediction.

Follow these rules:
- Keep solutions simple and low-friction.
- Do not overengineer.
- Do not add new platforms or tools unless explicitly approved.
- This project uses code-based deployment, not model-based deployment.
- The data architecture is Bronze / Silver / Gold.
- Gold must be one row per match.
- Features must be strictly time-aware and leakage-safe.
- Do not assume xG exists.
- Do not reimplement Elo formulas.
- Candidate models are Poisson, Negative Binomial, and XGBoost.
- The modeling target is goals / score distribution behavior, not direct W-D-L classification as the main objective.
- Match outcomes are derived later from score distributions or Monte Carlo simulation.
- All candidate model runs should eventually log to MLflow.
- Prefer local-first runnable code before adding cloud-specific dependencies.
- Stop after a meaningful milestone and summarize changes and blockers.